event.description:
The Vikings Exhibition: Interactive Exhibits, Artifacts & More -- Final Weeks

Viking culture comes alive as the largest collection of Viking artifacts ever displayed in North America invades Discovery Times Square. Nab these tickets in the exhibition's final weeks and skip the line, heading straight to the more than 500 treasures on display, including jewelry, swords and armor, and pagan religious iconography. Hands-on interactive activities put you in the daily life of the Vikings. Compete in authentic Viking games and test your strength with a reproduction of a Viking sword. Then take in the craftsmanship of full-scale models of Viking ships. With artifacts that have never been seen outside of Scandinavia, The Vikings Exhibition will have you feeling like a real Viking.

event.description: Children's Choir Fall 2016 August 31- December 7, 2016 All children grades preK through fifth grade are invited to register for the fall semester of Children's Choir. Choir meets on Wednesday afternoons from 4:30-5:30pm. Pre-Kindergarten/Kindergarten Music Time- Music activity for PreK and Kindergarten children. This is not a performance based choir, but a learning based music time which includes singing, playing instruments, and movement. Primary Choir- Students in first and second grade will enjoy a variety of activities including singing and small group offerings. Elementary Choir- Students in third through fifth grade will enjoy a variety of activities including singing and small group offerings. Children's Choir is a co-op program and parents of enrolled children are encouraged to volunteer. Adults are needed in each teaching room in order to meet our Safe Sanctuary policy. Please contact director for volunteer discount information.  When you register your child/children, please be sure to enter their names as the attendees (it defaults to the ticket buyers name). Thank you. For additional information, please contact Jennifer Boyd, Children's Choir Coordinator and Director at jenniferb@fumcwp.org, or 407-644-2906 x260.

event.description: Visit the Parkway Central Library’s Music Department on Sunday, August 14th for a rare chance to hear the musicians and students from Philadelphia’s Beyond the Bars, an organization teaching songs and music education to youth who are incarcerated. Beyond the Bars teachers will premiere the tracks at the heart of a month-long exhibition of audio the student musicians created.  You’ll hear performances, practice sessions leading up to concerts, and some music created especially for you.  Special for this opening, teachers will illuminate the sounds with commentary.  Music Department librarians will also feature a corresponding collection of print music and audiorecordings in response, and there might even be a special guest. Though this audio exhibition (which also closes the curtain on this summer’s collaborative Juvenile in Justice series) will live in the Music Department for anyone to listen to until September 4th, make sure to catch this opening to listen to the teachers and the students in this particularly timely soundtrack.  We hope it will shine a light on the faces of youth incarceration in the U.S, and inspire a dialogue about this institution's place in our twenty-first century communities. Beyond the Bars is a 501(c)3 organization dedicated to bringing musical education and instruments to incarcerated youth in Philadelphia.  Using instruments to create a safe space in which students can jam, practice, and learn how to play songs as well as its music theory elements and techniques, Beyond the Bars brings skills and the opportunity of creative expression to youths who find themselves victims of the criminal justice system. Grand Lobby & Music Department | Parkway Central Library1901 Vine Street | Philadelphia, PA 19103erefmus@freelibrary.org | 215-686-5316 A wheelchair ramp is located at the Library's Wood Street entrance; public elevator located on the Library's northeast side.
event.title: Beyond the Bars - Student Audio Exhibition

event.description: Ahoy, mateys! Feast your eye on the mottled crew of the scurvy Seaharse, and its blood-rusty master Captain Richard II Hooks. Shiver ye timbers at perils galore: Marauding radicals, ravenous cannibals, pirating queens, and the crimson cloak of the Indies Doctor Nemo. Gird your loins to encounter the great white colossus, wail in wonder at the booty in its bowels, and call me... The Nautical Tragedy of Dick III, is proudly presented by Quasimondo Physical Theatre. This original tour-de-farce mashes classic lit to a pregnable gruel; a swirling concoction of misfit mariners and twisted missions. Baited with puppetry, dance, clowns, and shanties, this high-sea adventure plunges into disparate diets, catching the bends of injustice to expunge what's gettin' our guts. Tharr she blows!
